              <br />
              <p>
                When "Edith," the mystical pen capable of rewriting the
                storylines of anime worlds, is stolen, the real world faces
                turmoil as dimensional rifts tear open, allowing anime
                characters to spill into reality.
              </p><br />
              <p>
                "Shimada Yuki," the story's protagonist—a legendary-class
                otaku—must team up with "Lecia," the guardian of anime world
                balance, to stop this chaos. However, capturing the escaped
                characters proves far from simple, as they must deal with
                countless mishaps and the quirky, troublesome personalities of
                these characters that give Yuki such headaches he's forced to
                seek help from "Shirogane Hime," a beautiful IT genius who
                excels at everything—especially her sharp tongue.
              </p><br />
              <p>
                What's worse is that the only way to send these displaced
                characters back to their worlds is to "capture their hearts."
                Will Yuki and his companions be able to win over all the
                characters' hearts and protect both worlds? Or will everything
                be rewritten... by the pen Edith?
